e severely beat and brainwashed her. Speaking deliberately, Ms. <PERSON> Nussbaum </PERSON> said she was cut off for years from her family and friends. During one period, <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> forbade her from leaving their apartment without his permission; she lost her job as an editor at <ORGANIZATION> Random </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> after repeatedly missing work because of black eyes, she said. `` Most of the time he made me sleep on the floor or in the bathtub if I had displeased him,'' she testified. Asked about her relationship with <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> in late 1983 or early 1984, Ms. <PERSON> Nussbaum </PERSON> replied, `` At that time, he began beating me severely.'' Prosecutors also submitted as evidence commandments that <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> issued to Ms. <PERSON> Nussbaum </PERSON> that came under the page heading, `` My goals in terms of <PERSON> Joel </PERSON>'s interest.'' He also would force her to write `` punishment lessons'' much like an errant pupil, writing each item 10 times, Ms. <PERSON> Nussbaum </PERSON> said. Among the things she was forced to write: `` Anger is destructive, not constructive.'' Judge <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Rothwax </PERSON> instructed the jury that <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> was on trial for the crime he is charged with `` and not for being a particular kind of person.'' The judge had agreed to a prosecution argument that the only way it could explain Ms. <PERSON> Nussbaum </PERSON> was incapable of saving the girl on the night <PERSON> Lisa </PERSON> was fatally injured was to show the extent to which she had been dominated by <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON>. Ms. <PERSON> Nussbaum </PERSON> testified Thursday that she did n't call for emergency help for <PERSON> Lisa </PERSON> because she thought <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON> had the power to heal the unconscious girl. The trial is scheduled to continue Monday.
