Qian </PERSON> told reporters Saturday that <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> would like to normalize relations `` on the basis of peace and coexistence,'' but without the close ties that once bound the two nations. `` It is necessary not to go back to the period of the 1950s, but it is also necessary not to return to confrontation,'' he said. During his 1-hour-40-minute meeting with <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> and more than six hours of meetings with <PERSON> Shevardnadze </PERSON>, <PERSON> Qian </PERSON> said the subjects discussed also included border trade and joint exploration of the Soviet Far East, as well as `` joint use of the labor force.''
