ld since the <ORGANIZATION> GATT </ORGANIZATION> was formed after World War II, including for the first time such issues as trade in services and protection of intellectual property such as patents and copyrights. The <ORGANIZATION> GATT </ORGANIZATION> is both an agreement and an organization which has a permanent headquarters in <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION>. The talks are taking place, as usual, largely behind closed doors. They are theoretically scheduled to end on Wednesday, but are likely to last into Thursday or possibly Friday. <PERSON> Samuels </PERSON> said the representatives of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> agreed at their meeting Saturday that an agreement should be completed Wednesday night so it can be ratified by the trade ministers on Thursday.
