 President-elect <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> and his staff are defending the way the transition office has handled appointments in a week that produced only one announcement. All week, there was speculation that <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> would make announcements on more Cabinet members, particularly for the <ORGANIZATION> defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> department </ORGANIZATION> and other national security jobs. But the only statement was that <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> would stay on as White House spokesman. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, who met Friday with foreign leaders and former presidential rivals, including <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, seemed to bristle when reporters asked him if his appointment process was stalled. `` There's no holdup. We're way ahead of schedule,'' he said, complaining about `` early, premature, needless speculation.''
